        [
          "Classification",
          "ITS",
          "Modeling student knowledge states and predicting learning-path related future behaviors from sequential interactions",
          "Implicitly successful future learning path / interaction relevance;",
          "EdNet: platform scale 784,309 students\n\nASSISTments 2017",
          "TOEIC prep platform (EdNet/Santa), math problem solving (ASSISTments)",
          "EdNet (KT1), ASSISTments 2017",
          "Timestamps, question/problem IDs, answers/correctness, skill labels, elapsed time, course progress, learning duration, interaction records; sequential temporal features extracted by CRNN",
          "Existing approaches struggle to model temporal dynamics and knowledge-point relationships effectively; prior methods use isolated CNN/RNN-style modeling and weaker knowledge association / reward design",
          "Hybrid framework combining CRNN for sequential feature extraction, Transformer for knowledge-point association, and RL for path optimizationHybrid framework combining CRNN for sequential feature extraction, Transformer for knowledge-point association, and RL for path optimization",
          "Adam optimizer; batch size 32; early stopping; CRNN with 3x3 filters + LSTM (128 hidden units); Transformer with 4 heads and 256-d embeddings",
          "Proposed model, DKT, SAKT, BKT",
          "Holdout Method (70/15/15)",
          "EdNet\n\n{F1-Score: 0.912 - Proposed Model, HITS@K: 0.876 - Proposed Model}\n\nAST17\n{F1-Score: 0.898 - Proposed Model}",
          "Experiment 1 is explicitly knowledge tracing. Stronger than baselines on both EdNet and ASSISTments.",
          "Not a pure KT model; target is less cleanly defined than “next answer correctness”; metrics used for KT experiment are F1/HITS@K, not the more usual AUC/RMSE despite the text mentioning them elsewhere; student counts for experimental subsets are not clearly specified"
